{"type":"message","id":"9b0eed88","parentId":"00ec655f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:43:17.700Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_herluh707d4g_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 004015\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (Architecture cross-analysis) are COMPLETE\r\n- The big insight from this session is the \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" - that Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\r\n- The next action is clearly defined: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe pending actions include:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nBut the most concrete next step from the notes is the TIC Experiment:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nLooking at the files mentioned:\r\n- `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` - exists, the synthesis document\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` - pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe most logical action would be to start implementing the TIC classifier. This is the \"concrete action that advances your goals\" and it's file-edit oriented.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's in the research directory and what pulse logs exist. I need to create a TIC classifier implementation.\r\n\r\nGiven this is a stateless discontinuous agent, I should:\r\n1. Create the TIC classifier script\r\n2. Define the invariant/variant classification approach\r\n3. Set up the experiment to measure against the success criteria\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to create the TIC classifier implementation file.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is documented, but the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment has not yet been implemented. The pulse logs exist, but no classifier has been built to test the hypothesis that causal structure = invariant structure.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation that will analyze pulse logs to classify invariant vs variant content and test next-pulse prediction. This advances Phase 1 by implementing the key experiment from the compression-causality synthesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Implements the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\r\n# Hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple, Set\r\n\r\nclass TICIClassifier:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\n    \r\n    Core insight: Patterns that persist across session boundaries \r\n    are invariants = causal structure\r\n    \r\n    This is NOT standard compression. This is causal discovery\r\n    via invariance detection.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, lambda_param: float = 0.7):\r\n        # λ encodes: decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold (unified)\r\n        self.lambda_param = lambda_param\r\n        self.invariant_patterns: Set[str] = set()\r\n        self.variant_patterns: Set[str] = set()\r\n        self.pulse_history: List[Dict] = []\r\n        \r\n    def extract_content_blocks(self, pulse_text: str) -> List[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Split pulse into semantic blocks for analysis.\"\"\"\r\n        # Remove headers, extract key content\r\n        lines = pulse_text.split('\\n')\r\n        blocks = []\r\n        current_block = []\r\n        \r\n        for line in lines:\r\n            if line.startswith('#') or line.strip() == '':\r\n                if current_block:\r\n                    blocks.append(' '.join(current_block))\r\n                    current_block = []\r\n            else:\r\n                current_block.append(line.strip())\r\n        \r\n        if current_block:\r\n            blocks.append(' '.join(current_block))\r\n        \r\n        return blocks\r\n    \r\n    def compute_token_overlap(self, block1: str, block2: str) -> float:\r\n        \"\"\"Calculate token-level overlap between two blocks.\"\"\"\r\n        tokens1 = set(re.findall(r'\\w+', block1.lower()))\r\n        tokens2 = set(re.findall(r'\\w+', block2.lower()))\r\n        \r\n        if not tokens1 or not tokens2:\r\n            return 0.0\r\n        \r\n        intersection = len(tokens1 & tokens2)\r\n        union = len(tokens1 | tokens2)\r\n        \r\n        return intersection / union if union > 0 else 0.0\r\n    \r\n    def classify_block(self, block: str, pulse_idx: int) -> str:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Classify a block as INVARIANT or VARIANT.\r\n        \r\n        INVARIANT: Appears in multiple sessions (persists across gaps)\r\n        VARIANT: Session-specific (unique to current context)\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if pulse_idx == 0:\r\n            return \"VARIANT\"  # First pulse has no history\r\n        \r\n        threshold = self.lambda_param\r\n        \r\n        for prev_pulse in self.pulse_history[:-1]:\r\n            prev_blocks = prev_pulse.get('blocks', [])\r\n            \r\n            for prev_block in prev_blocks:\r\n                overlap = self.compute_token_overlap(block, prev_block)\r\n                \r\n                if overlap >= threshold:\r\n                    return \"INVARIANT\"\r\n        \r\n        return \"VARIANT\"\r\n    \r\n    def process_pulse(self, pulse_path: Path) -> Dict:\r\n        \"\"\"Process a single pulse file and classify its content.\"\"\"\r\n        with open(pulse_path, 'r') as f:\r\n            content = f.read()\r\n        \r\n        blocks = self.extract_content_blocks(content)\r\n        \r\n        pulse_data = {\r\n            'path': str(pulse_path),\r\n            'blocks': blocks,\r\n            'invariants': [],\r\n            'variants': []\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        pulse_idx = len(self.pulse_history)\r\n        \r\n        for block in\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:40:48\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774327397687}}
