{"type":"message","id":"b8714c5c","parentId":"98dee5cc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:43:38.547Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_eftwfpkh8sm8_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 004214\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a key insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. The NEXT ACTION is: Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n4. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. To do this, I need to:\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs\r\n2. Implement a classifier that identifies invariants vs variants\r\n3. Test prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist and what data I have to work with. The most recent pulse log mentioned is `pulse_2026-03-24 004015.md`.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. First examine the existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create the TIC experiment implementation\r\n\r\nLet me create an implementation plan for the TIC classifier. I'll create a Python script or PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Loads the last N pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant patterns (things that stay the same across pulses)\r\n3. Identifies variant patterns (things that change)\r\n4. Tests classification accuracy\r\n5. Tests next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nI'll create a concrete implementation file for this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is compelling but unimplemented. The TIC experiment requires a working classifier to validate the hypothesis that causal structure discovery and compression are the same problem.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment script that analyzes pulse logs to classify invariant vs variant patterns and tests next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```python\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom typing import List, Tuple, Dict\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_PULSES = 5\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    def __init__(self):\r\n        self.invariants = {}      # token -> count across all pulses\r\n        self.variants = {}        # token -> variance score\r\n        self.pulse_signatures = []  # List of normalized pulse tokens\r\n        \r\n    def load_pulses(self) -> List[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse log files sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n        pulse_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=os.path.getmtime)\r\n        pulses = []\r\n        for f in pulse_files:\r\n            content = f.read_text()\r\n            pulses.append(self._tokenize(content))\r\n        return pulses\r\n    \r\n    def _tokenize(self, text: str) -> List[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract meaningful tokens from pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n        # Remove timestamps, filepaths, common boilerplate\r\n        text = re.sub(r'\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}[\\s\\d:]+', '<TS>', text)\r\n        text = re.sub(r'[a-zA-Z]:\\\\[^\\s]+', '<PATH>', text)\r\n        text = re.sub(r'[a-z_/]+\\.(md|ps1|txt)', '<FILE>', text)\r\n        # Split into tokens (words/phrases)\r\n        tokens = re.findall(r'\\b\\w{3,}\\b', text.lower())\r\n        return tokens\r\n    \r\n    def compute_invariance_scores(self, pulses: List[List[str]]) -> Dict[str, float]:\r\n        \"\"\"Compute invariance score for each token: 1 = always present, 0 = never.\"\"\"\r\n        if not pulses:\r\n            return {}\r\n        all_tokens = set(token for p in pulses for token in p)\r\n        n_pulses = len(pulses)\r\n        scores = {}\r\n        for token in all_tokens:\r\n            count = sum(1 for p in pulses if token in p)\r\n            scores[token] = count / n_pulses\r\n        return scores\r\n    \r\n    def classify_token(self, token: str, score: float, threshold: float = 0.6) -> str:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify token as INVARIANT or VARIANT based on score.\"\"\"\r\n        return \"INVARIANT\" if score >= threshold else \"VARIANT\"\r\n    \r\n    def extract_invariant_features(self, pulse: List[str], scores: Dict[str, float]) -> List[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract only invariant tokens from a pulse.\"\"\"\r\n        return [t for t in pulse if scores.get(t, 0) >= 0.6]\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next_pulse(self, current_invariants: List[str], \r\n                          future_pulses: List[List[str]]) -> List[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Predict invariants in next pulse based on current pattern.\"\"\"\r\n        if not future_pulses:\r\n            return current_invariants\r\n        # Next pulse invariants = tokens stable across future pulses\r\n        future_scores = self.compute_invariance_scores(future_pulses)\r\n        return [t for t in current_invariants if future_scores.get(t, 0) >= 0.6]\r\n    \r\n    def run_experiment(self) -> Tuple[float, float]:\r\n        \"\"\"Run full TIC experiment. Returns (classification_acc, prediction_acc).\"\"\"\r\n        pulses = self.load_pulses()\r\n        if len(pulses) < MIN_PULSES:\r\n            print(f\"Need {MIN_PULSES} pulses, found {len(pulses)}\")\r\n            return 0.0, 0.0\r\n        \r\n        # Split: train on first 80%, test on last 20%\r\n\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:42:43"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,